<br>
1) How the hell does playing a Female Character = Leading you on.<br>
<br>
Proper distance from the game people. If you wanna play a girlie go for it. Shintou personally doesn't like women that much anyhow, but he gives things to people that need it on the dark side.. reguardless of sex. But I cannot see how simply playing a toon with boobs leads people on.<br>
<br>
2) I believe in a Don't Ask/Don't Tell because I Dont Care.<br>
<br>
All goes back to proper distance from the game. If someone wants to play a girlie, I don't care. Thats their deal, I'm not going to go around asking (Well I have before sometimes just for curiosity's sake, but I have stopped doing this) every female toon ((Hey, are you a guy IRL?))<br>
The Ranger said he had a bit of a problem RP flirting with a girl charrie that was acually a guy. That problem disapears if you just don't know. Just as long as you know better then to expect some kind of OOC relationship throught roleplaying (Got forbit someone falls in love with a toon on EQ just to find out that its a guy IRL), you should be fine just not knowing. <br>
<br>
