So if they don't like the fact that you're a guy playing a female character, tell em to fuck off.  Two of the best friends I have had in this game were guys playing females.    When I found out, it was a small shock, but they were still the same two kick ass Rangers when I logged in.  And I even asked one to RP marry after I found out.  And I most certainly like women in real life. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wolfaykin>Wolfaykin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Strength through Wounding<br>Roose's Boytoy</span><br>  Posts: 518<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/24/03 2:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3921.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: In the eyes of the FV Community...Id like to know</span><hr size=1> I'm impressed.<br>
