But it hasn't.  Wow.  Maturity wins for once?  *grins*<br>
<br>
Seriously, I have played female characters before (actually about a 60/40 split female to male) and I have dealt with some immature people who were insulted or angry when they found out I was a man in real life.  I have read long flame posts on other boards about how men who play female characters are all repressed homosexuals or mentally sick in some way.<br>
<br>
I've never understood that.  For non roleplayers, it is your toon.  It doesn't matter what sex it is.  For roleplayers, it is your character, not yourself.   When I storytell World of Darkness games, my players know their characters are not allowed to just be themselves as a Vampire, or they die the final death rather quickly.  For me, the fun is becoming someone else, even if it just for an hour, and watching others explore their roles, growing into them, perfecting them.<br>
<br>
Who cares if a man plays a female character.  Who cares if that female character flirts with male characters <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>in character?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Only possible way I could see it as a problem is if you pretended to be a female in real life, and lead them on OOC.  But simply existing and roleplaying as a female is not leading anyone on.  <br>
